                                <div class="max-w-[29.25rem] text-color-7 lg:max-w-full">Tax planning is essential when it comes to major financial events, such as buying a home, starting a business, or planning for retirement. These events often have significant tax implications, and proper tax planning can help you make informed decisions to minimize the tax impact. For example, understanding the tax deductions and credits available for homebuyers or the tax implications of different retirement account options can help you plan strategically and save on taxes, allowing you to achieve your financial goals more effectively.</div>
